import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.hist(data['group_size'], bins=20, color='green')
    plt.axvline(data['group_size'].mean(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label=f"Mean: {data['group_size'].mean():0.2f}")
    plt.axvline(data['group_size'].median(), color='blue', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label=f"Median: {data['group_size'].median():0.2f}")
    plt.legend()
    plt.xlabel('Group Size')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of group sizes?')
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    group_type_counts = data['group_type'].value_counts()
    ax = group_type_counts.plot(kind='bar', color='blue')
    ax.set_xlabel('Group Type')
    ax.set_ylabel('Count')
    ax.axhline(y=group_type_counts.max(), color='red', linestyle='--', label='Max Count: {:.2f}'.format(group_type_counts.max()))
    ax.legend()
    plt.title('What is the most common group type?', wrap=True)
    return plt

data = pd.read_csv('lookup_groups.csv')
chart = plot(data)
```

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
import seaborn as sns

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['age'] = pd.to_numeric(data['age'], errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['age'])]
    fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(8,6))
    sns.boxplot(x='age', data=data, ax=ax, color='skyblue')
    ax.axvline(data['age'].mean(), color='red', linestyle='--', label=f'Mean: {data["age"].mean():.2f}')
    ax.axvline(data['age'].median(), color='green', linestyle='--', label=f'Median: {data["age"].median():.2f}')
    ax.set_xlabel('Age')
    ax.set_title('What is the average age of group members?')
    ax.legend()
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    gender_counts = data['gender'].value_counts()
    labels = gender_counts.index.tolist()
    sizes = gender_counts.values.tolist()
    colors = ['pink', 'lightblue']
    fig1, ax1 = plt.subplots()
    ax1.pie(sizes, colors=colors, labels=labels, autopct='%1.1f%%', startangle=90)
    ax1.axis('equal')
    plt.title('What is the gender distribution of group members?', wrap=True)
    plt.legend(title='Gender', loc='center left', bbox_to_anchor=(1, 0, 0.5, 1))
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data = data[['group_size', 'group_type']]
    plt.scatter(data['group_size'], data['group_type'], alpha=0.5)
    plt.xlabel('Group Size')
    plt.ylabel('Group Type')
    plt.title('What is the relationship between group size and group type?', wrap=True)
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
